article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 68, Texas-San Antonio 59
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Jordan Glynn had 17 points and 11 rebounds Saturday as Stephen F. Austin rallied for a 68-59 victory over UTSA. Desmond Haymon added a career-high 15 points off the bench for the Lumberjacks (11-4, 2-1 Southland), and Dion Prewster also had a career-high with 13 points -- all in the second half. Devin Gibson led UTSA (7-8, 1-2) with 18 points. Melvin Johnson III and Jeromie Hill had 11 each. Stephen F. Austin trailed 9-0 in the opening minutes and 29-25 at halftime. The Lumberjacks didn't take their first lead until there was 15:45 left in the game when Glynn hit a jump shot to cap an 8-0 run. Stephen F. Austin used another 8-0 run to go on top 48-41 with 6:04 left, then pulled away for good with an 11-3 run that made the score 64-53 with 1:30 remaining. The Lumberjacks made only 2 of 11 3-point attempts in the game, but were 20 for 26 at the free-throw line compared to 13 of 19 for UTSA.
